      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KING COREY (7) faded out when tackling stronger company last time but will relish the class drop having won two in succession at this circuit and distance prior. The driver has some work to do from this wide starting position but with even luck he has the talent to return to the winners' list. DANCING WITH MY EX (4) produced a good effort at this circuit and distance last week when he came from the widest barrier and finished third, beaten less than 3 metres. A lower draw sees him in contention again. CARIBBEAN RUNA (1) has been coming from wider or second row barriers of late but was fourth from this draw the last time she raced here. LARRIKIN LENNY (8) hasn't had a lot go to plan of late but came from a similar barrier to win at this circuit and distance last month so is capable of better.",
